
# Installation Guide

This guide will help you set up your environment for the project.

## Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following before proceeding:

- A Unix-like operating system (e.g., Ubuntu)
- Sudo privileges

## Steps to Install

### 1. Update and Install Dependencies

Update your package list and install essential packages:

```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y build-essential g++ cmake libopencv-dev curl sudo tzdata
```

### 2. Install Node.js

Install Node.js version 18.x by running the following commands:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
```

### 3. Set Up the Working Directory

Ensure that you have the correct working directory for your project. This step may involve cloning a repository or creating necessary directories.

### 4. Make the Build Script Executable

Change the permissions of the `build.sh` script to make it executable:

```bash
chmod +x build.sh
```

### 5. Run the Build Script

Execute the `build.sh` script to complete the setup:

```bash
./build.sh
```
